docs.abstract: Lawmakers and Sam Altman, the chief executive of OpenAI, agreed that artificial intelligence should be regulated. How to do that remains an open question.
docs.snippet: Lawmakers and Sam Altman, the chief executive of OpenAI, agreed that artificial intelligence should be regulated. How to do that remains an open question.
docs.lead_paragraph: The fireworks that usually pop when technology executives testify before Congress were noticeably absent from yesterday’s Senate hearing on artificial intelligence. Instead, lawmakers questioned Sam Altman, the C.E.O. of OpenAI, for three hours in what appeared to be a genuine effort to understand the growing importance, and the dangers, of artificial intelligence.

headline.main: Washington Confronts the Challenge of Policing A.I.

docs.abstract: Even after the sale of First Republic, investors are worried about challenges that regional banks still face, imperiling the economy.
docs.snippet: Even after the sale of First Republic, investors are worried about challenges that regional banks still face, imperiling the economy.
docs.lead_paragraph: After JPMorgan Chase secured a deal to buy the embattled First Republic, the banking giant’s chief, Jamie Dimon, asserted that the market turmoil set off by Silicon Valley Bank’s collapse was at an end. “This part of the crisis is over,” he told analysts on Monday.

headline.main: Why Many on Wall Street Fear the Banking Crisis Isn’t Over

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Ravi Mattu, Bernhard Warner, Sarah Kessler, Michael J. de la Merced and Lauren Hirsch

docs.abstract: Is Bluesky the long-awaited heir to Twitter?
docs.snippet: Is Bluesky the long-awaited heir to Twitter?
docs.lead_paragraph: The Twitter look-alike Bluesky, started by the former Twitter chief executive Jack Dorsey, is doing the impossible: making social media fun again.
